2017 WW46 Bakerville/SKX-D Engineering Release Announcement (\r\n BKC #34)

\r\n \r\n \r\n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\r\n \r\n
\r\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW46 Bakerville/SKX-D Engineering release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\r\n \r\n ESXi6.5/\r\n \r\n RHEL7.3/\r\n \r\n WS2016\r\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Li, Feng Y.

  • No HW rework need for Yuba City\r\n fab3 board.
    • \r\n
  • jumper setting refers to\r\n this link.
    • \r\n

 Work\r\naround:

    \r\n
  • Secure Boot only can run in\r\n UEFI mode, so if we want secure boot can work and let bios load UEFI\r\n Oprom, we need Disable this option. 
    • \r\n

EDKII\r\nMenu -> Boot Options -> EFI INT10 workaround

  • When you flash onboard Aspeed\r\n BMC, in order to detect onboard dTPM in AC cycle, you need run below IPMI\r\n command in UEFI Shell:
